      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: use configured work days for weekly pace",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- use configured work days for standard weekly pace calculations\n- keep historical Codex pacing unchanged when historical data is available\n- compute ETA in work time and map it back to wall-clock time\n- avoid declaring zero usage safe before the first configured workday has elapsed\n- use the existing persisted `weeklyProgressWorkDays` value for both weekly markers and fallback pace/ETA; this unified behavior is intentional\n\nSupersedes #1357 because repository CI would not start for the fork head. Preserves @pstanton237's commits and authorship.\n\nFixes #1356.\n\n## Validation\n\n- focused pace, historical-authority, settings, menu-model, and localization tests\n- timezone stress under `Pacific/Auckland`\n- complete deterministic inventory: 3,947 tests across 426 suites\n- `make check`\n- `swift build`\n- ad-hoc packaged debug app from exact head `166dc073`; strict deep codesign verification passed\n- built-app proof: selected 4 days, Off, and 5 days in Display settings; verified persistence after restart; exercised the real CLI-backed Codex account and menu refresh; the current account exposed no weekly rate-limit event, so historical/fallback menu rendering remains covered by focused regressions\n- autoreview clean\n- Public Model Identifier Gate: PASS; no account payloads or model identifiers included in public proof\n",
